(1, 1, '2012-07-20 09:08:33', '2012-07-20 09:08:33', 'Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!', 'Hello world!', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-world', '', '', '2012-07-24 09:43:55', '2012-07-24 09:43:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost/imhf/?p=1', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(2, 1, '2012-07-20 09:08:33', '2012-07-20 09:08:33', 'This is an example page. It''s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I''m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin'' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://localhost/imhf/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'Sample Page', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'sample-page', '', '', '2012-07-27 02:59:53', '2012-07-27 02:59:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost/imhf/?page_id=2', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(4, 1, '2012-07-20 10:15:50', '2012-07-20 10:15:50', '<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">Our Mission statement is: <em>"To support the Indiana Masonic Home by holding in trust undesignated endowment funds given for the benefit of the Home, and to manage these funds to achieve maximum returns consistent with prudent investment practices. The net income from such trust will be paid annually to the Home to support its purposes and needs. The Foundation will provide trust services for funds which have been received and designated for special purpose of the Home."</em></span></p>\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">The Indiana Masonic Home Foundation (IMHF) was established in 1936 to further implement financial support of the Home. We are a separate corporation with a separate Board of Directors to oversee our operations and investments.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">Further, the Foundation engages in promotional and public relation activities to increase the assets and properties held by the Foundation; communicates to the Masonic membership the charitable need, purpose, and benefits of the Indiana Masonic Home, and provides the necessary professional guidance to help Freemasonry be successful in its benevolent efforts. This is achieved through the joint effort of the Foundation, its staff and Directors, the Home and its staff, and all the brothers and sisters of the family of Freemasonry.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"> It is important to know that the Foundation fund, gives only its net income or interest to the Home each year. Therefore, gifts to the Foundation have never been spent. Also, gifts are tax deductible as described in section 501 (c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;"> Located on 300 magnificent acres, the Indiana Masonic Home is conveniently located in the friendly town of Franklin, just south of Indianapolis. Since its beginning in 1916, it has been a retirement community serving all Indiana Masonic families.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">Whether you are a senior who is completely independent, one that seeks occasional assistance, or one that requires comprehensive health care, the Indiana Masonic Home campus is able to meet your needs. We offer a variety of living arrangements, and different levels of care depending on your needs. Make yourself at home in one of our cottages, duplexes, or one of the one, or two bedroom apartments. You no longer need to be concerned about the daily chores of cooking, housekeeping, laundry and yard work. The Medical Center provides one of the finest long term health care facilities in the Midwest. This 160 bed center provides comprehensive care and offers private and semi-private Quarters.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">There are many activities for Masonic Home residents. On the grounds of the campus are Kresge Chapel and Ransford Chapel where Sunday services are conducted to accommodate many faiths and physical requirements of the residents. During the week you will have the opportunity to be active in exercise groups, prayer circle, coffee and social hours, crafts, ceramics, cards, concerts, outings and games. You will make many new friends. Day trips and shopping trips are also planned. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;">Not only will you find a new home and friends here, but you will be surrounded by beautiful campus acres. When entering our campus you will see the distinctive, impressive arch and view lovely manicured flowered gardens and the incredible elevated garden fountain. Also, on the campus are the Indiana Masonic Library and Museum, the Marvin Isley Bell Tower, a greenhouse, the Indiana Masonic Supplies gift shop, and offices of the Grand Chapter, O.E.S. and Indiana Demolay. </span>', 'About IMHF', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about-imhf', '', '', '2012-07-24 02:00:40', '2012-07-24 02:00:40', '', 0, 'http://localhost/imhf/?page_id=4', 0, 'page', '', 0),
