thors being Baldacci, Clancy, Flynn and Grisholm. He enjoys golf and spending a great deal of his time with his nine year old black lab, Mr. Atlas. Ken says that he has spent most of his life in the non-profit world because he is a firm believer that the most successful people in the world are those who help others along the way. He went on to say he is extremely proud to be on the team here at the Indiana Masonic Home Foundation.\r\n\r\n<strong><big>Danyelle Hoshauer</big></strong>, <a href="dhoshauer@imhf.org">dhoshauer@imhf.org</a>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-142" style="margin-right: 10px;" title="danyelle" src="http://www.scxserv.com/imhf/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/danyelle-167x300.jpg" alt="" width="167" height="300" />Danyelle Hoshauer joined the Foundation staff as Fundraising Associate on May 1st. She will be working alongside other foundation staff to build a comprehensive fund raising program, with the main goal increasing major gifts to the Foundation.\r\n\r\nDanyelle began her career in non-profit with Indiana State University Foundation, working her way from Operations to Development. She gained extensive experience working with Annual Giving staff, and was responsible for growing the President?s Society group and assisted in Major Gift work in conjunction with the first comprehensive campaign for ISU. She spent a little over a year working in Sales and Marketing at Westminster Village in Terre Haute where she developed a deep appreciation for those who provide care for seniors. She has also worked in staffing development and corporate sales roles.\r\n\r\nDanyelle is proud to, once again, join the non-profit world and be a part of an organization that is caring for its members and families.\r\n\r\nIn her spare time, she has participates volunteer activities, including Ronald McDonald house and the YMCA, and particpates in different league sports.\r\n\r\n<strong><big>Steve Sonafrank</big></strong>, <a href="ssonafrank@imhf.org">ssonafrank@imhf.org</a>\r\n<img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-143" style="margin-right: 10px;" title="steve" src="http://www.scxserv.com/imhf/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/steve-202x300.jpg" alt="" width="202" height="300" />A native of Bunker Hill, Indiana, Steve attended Maconaquah High School and graduated from Indiana University in 1988, where he played trombone in the Marching Hundred and earned a bachelor of science degree in education. He later taught English at Maconaquah High School and served as speech coach. He most recently served as a sales associate at W.H. Paige &amp; Company in Indianapolis.\r\n\r\nHe has served as an elder at Irvington Presbyterian Church, board member at Epworth Forest Choir School, and president of the board for the Indiana University Marching Hundred Alumni Band.\r\n\r\nBrother Sonafrank was raised a Master Mason in 2002 at Bunker Hill Lodge No.683, where he is a Past Master. He served concurrently as Worshipful Master, Grand Steward &amp; Tyler, and Indiana Masonic Home board member in 2006-07. In the Scottish Rite, he is currently Master of Ceremonies in the officer line of the Indianapolis Chapter of Rose Croix.\r\n\r\nIn his spare time, he enjoys playing trombone in the Scottish Rite Orchestra as well as in the Christ Presbyterian Church brass ensemble. He follows both Indiana University athletics and the Indianapolis Colts. When IU won the national basketball championship in 1987, he witnessed the victory from the front row of the IU basketball band in the New Orleans Superdome. He also enjoys swimming, biking, yard work, and tinkering with his antique Maytag wringer washing machine.\r\n\r\nSteve and his wife Jenny first met while college students in the IU Marching Hundred. They were married at Irvington Presbyterian Church in 1996 and live in Indianapolis.\r\n\r\n<strong><big>Kate Miller</big></strong>, <a href="kmiller@imhf.org">kmiller@imhf.org</a>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-196 alignleft" style="margin-right: 10px;" title="kate-portrait" src="http://www.scxserv.com/imhf/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/kate-portrait.jpg" alt="" width="240" height="275" />Kate Miller joined our staff as Development Associate on August 22, 2011. Along with Ken, she will be directly involved in building a comprehensive fundraising program with a main goal to increase giving to the IMHF. Kate most recently graduated from IUPUI, receiving her Bachelor’s Degree in Public Management.\r\n\r\nShe will be a key player in the development team given her background in organizational planning and her expertise in database management. She has a very extensive customer relation’s background, as well as many years of experience in the volunteer sector of the nonprofit world contributing her time to organizations such as the Boys and Girls club, Indianapolis Public Schools, and Habitat for Humanity. She has always maintained an interest and participation in nonprofit development, stewardship and sustainability.\r\n\r\nAs well as staying active in the community, she enjoys staying active in her own life; running, biking, and coaching youth soccer. Kate plans to continue her active role as a volunteer. She is honored to continue her professional career at the IMHF and to be a part of our mission to support the Indiana Masonic Home.\r\n\r\n<strong><big>Cherie Cannon</big></strong>, <a href="ccannon@imhf.org">ccannon@imhf.org</a>\r\n<img class="size-full wp-image-223 alignleft" style="margin-right: 10px;" title="cherie" src="http://www.scxserv.com/imhf/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/cherie.jpg" alt="" width="201" height="300" />\r\nCherie Cannon became the Office Manager for IMHF in 2007. She brought with her several years of accounting experience, along with a brief medical background. As a longtime member of the American Legion Women’s Auxiliary Group, Post 45, in Noblesville Indiana, Cherie volunteers and enjoys being involved with many activities that support the community and provide comfort for veterans and their families in need.\r\n\r\nCherie, a mother of 3 children, ages 23, 20, and 12, actively participates with her family in their extracurricular activities, so much so that she has been a cheerleading coach, soccer coach, and football team mom. She served on the PTA committee to organize outside school activities and fundraising. For many years Cherie attended Bethel AME church in Noblesville where she joined the choir and served as junior pastor for 2 yrs. She recently began attending Kingsway church in Avon. Cherie will continue her education at IVY Tech community college in the Fall/Winter of 2012, pursuing Human Resources with a concentration in Accounting. She will complete her application for membership at the Plainfield OES Chapter in the spring, and looks forward to the upcoming years with IMHF.', 'Staff', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '28-revision-35', '', '', '2012-08-27 19:19:20', '2012-08-27 19:19:20', '', 28, 'http://www.scxserv.com/imhf/28-revision-35/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
